# Tailwind CSS Best Practices

## Utility-First Approach
- **Composition**: Build complex components from utility classes
- **Avoid custom CSS**: Use utilities instead of writing custom CSS
- **@apply sparingly**: Use @apply only for extracting component patterns
- **Inline utilities**: Prefer inline utilities over extracted classes

## Class Organization
- **Logical grouping**: Group related utilities (layout, spacing, colors, typography)
- **Responsive design**: Mobile-first, then add responsive modifiers (sm:, md:, lg:)
- **State variants**: Use hover:, focus:, active: for interactive states
- **Dark mode**: Use dark: prefix for dark mode styles

## Configuration
- **Extend theme**: Extend default theme, don't replace it
- **Custom colors**: Define brand colors in theme
- **Custom spacing**: Add project-specific spacing values
- **Plugins**: Use official plugins when needed

## Component Patterns
- **Reusable classes**: Extract common patterns with @layer components
- **Variants**: Use @apply for component variants
- **Base styles**: Define base styles in @layer base
- **Utilities**: Add custom utilities in @layer utilities

## Performance
- **Purge CSS**: Configure content paths for tree-shaking
- **JIT mode**: Use JIT mode for faster builds
- **Production build**: Always build for production
- **CDN**: Don't use CDN in production

## Responsive Design
- **Mobile-first**: Design for mobile first, then scale up
- **Breakpoints**: Use standard breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl)
- **Container**: Use container class for max-width layouts
- **Grid/Flexbox**: Use grid and flex utilities for layouts

## Accessibility
- **Focus states**: Always style focus states
- **Color contrast**: Ensure sufficient color contrast
- **Screen readers**: Use sr-only for screen reader text
- **Semantic HTML**: Use with semantic HTML elements

## Integration
- **PostCSS**: Configure PostCSS properly
- **Autoprefixer**: Use autoprefixer for browser compatibility
- **CSS imports**: Import Tailwind directives correctly
- **Framework integration**: Follow framework-specific setup

## Dark Mode
- **Class strategy**: Use class strategy for manual toggle
- **Media strategy**: Use media strategy for system preference
- **Consistent**: Apply dark mode consistently across app
- **Testing**: Test both light and dark modes

## Don't
- Don't use inline styles
- Don't create custom CSS files for every component
- Don't use arbitrary values excessively
- Don't ignore responsive design
- Don't forget to configure purge/content paths
